    "summary": "Studying management for my bachelor's and being interested in the specific subject of human resources encouraged me to enhance my knowledge in a field that could deepen my understanding of the behavior of individuals in communities and groups. I gained this knowledge, doing my master's degree in social sciences research with a focus on sociology.  Between my Master's and the Ph.D. that I am doing currently, I associated and/or managed about 10 research projects in which I applied a combination of knowledge I have been equipped with during both my degrees. I have been always interested in applying sociological theories and research methodology in the subjects related to inequality and its consequences, particularly for individuals' mental well-being. Also, conducting some projects focused on groups who are disadvantaged and excluded/marginalized due to their different ethnicity, gender, socioeconomic status, etc., I became interested in the subject of social integrity. Currently, in my doctoral thesis, I am focusing on studying the interplay of subjective and objective inequality and mental well-being. \n\nFurthermore, doing my master's degree in Social Sciences Methodology, a part of my professional interests is learning and applying different methods in social inquiries. I do use some quantitative, and also mixed-methods to gain a comprehensive and deep understanding of the investigated phenomenon, from a dynamic perspective.",
