        {
            "title": "designing strategies for increasing the social cohesion among neighbours from different cultures living in complexes in Mashhad, Iran",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 3,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2017
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 3,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2018
                }
            },
            "description": "As the second biggest city of Iran and the first religious and tourist attraction city of Iran, Mashhad is an attractive city for job seekers from other cities offering numerous and various job opportunities. This fact has brought about a huge amount of immigrants from different regions of the country with different cultures and ethnicities in Mashhad during the recent decades. One of the problems of this multiculturalism is the conflicts among neighbours specifically in marginalised parts of the city where are mostly occupied by new immigrants. The aim of this study was to find some strategies to increase social correlation among neighbours living in apartments and complexes in marginalised parts of the city (Mashhad).",
            "contributors": [
                {
                    "type": "standardizedContributor",
                    "first_name": "Atefeh",
                    "last_name": "Bagherianziarat",
                    "name": null,
                    "headline": "Ph.D. student and Research Associate"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Recognizing the main social problems related to urbanicity among citizens living in marginalized parts of the city (Mashhad, Iran)",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2016
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2017
                }
            },
            "description": "One of the main issues that the city council of Mashhad always has to deal with is the various social problems that exist in marginalized parts of the city partially due to its multicultural context. To centralize and enhance the efficiency of the efforts of the city council to manage these problems, we conducted this study to distinguish the fundamental challenges which also lead to other problems. We used a mixed-method approach in this study and recognized the eight most important social problems according to the opinions of specialists, local managers, and local citizens.",
            "contributors": [
                {
                    "type": "standardizedContributor",
                    "first_name": "Atefeh",
                    "last_name": "Bagherianziarat",
                    "name": null,
                    "headline": "Ph.D. student and Research Associate"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Evaluating the efficiency of training organised by Mashhad city council to increase the social participation among citizens",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 2,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2015
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 3,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2016
                }
            },
            "description": "According to the findings of some previous studies, one of the main reasons recognized for the lower efficiency of the city-wide projects run by city management in Mashhad was lower social participation among citizens specifically among whom are living in parts of the city that are mostly occupied by immigrants.  Due to encouraging the targeted groups of citizens to have more social participation, Mashhad city council granted some workshops and lifetime learning courses that took place during one year. In this study, we conducted evaluative research to assess the efficiency of these pieces of training. We used a mixed method approach in this study.",
